<div class="help-container">
  <div class="help-header">
    <h1>🎵 Help & Guidance</h1>
    <p>Your complete guide to using the Singing Cadets management system</p>
  </div>

  <% if user_signed_in? %>
    <% if current_user.user? %>
      <!-- MEMBERS SECTION -->
      <section class="help-role-section">
        <div class="role-header">
          <h2>👤 Member Guide</h2>
          <p>Everything you need to know as a member</p>
        </div>

        <div class="help-grid">
          <!-- EVENTS -->
          <div class="help-card">
            <div class="card-header">
              <h3>📅 Events</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-content">
              <details>
                <summary class="card-summary"><strong>View Upcoming Events</strong></summary>
                <p>Click <%= link_to "Events", internal_events_path %> in the top navigation. Events are sorted with upcoming events first.</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Event Details:</strong> Click any event to see the full details</li>
                  <li><strong>Time & Location:</strong> Find when and where the event takes place</li>
                  <li><strong>Attendance Status:</strong> See if you're marked as attended, excused, or absent</li>
                  <li><strong>Quick Actions:</strong> Submit an excuse directly from the event page if needed</li>
                </ul>
              </details>

              <details>
                <summary class="card-summary"><strong>Check In to an Event</strong></summary>
                <p>Mark yourself as attended for an event:</p>
                <ol>
                  <li>Go to <%= link_to "Events", internal_events_path %> and click the event you're attending</li>
                  <li><strong>Self Check-in via Code:</strong> If the organizer provided a check-in code, enter it on the event page to automatically mark yourself as attended</li>
                  <li><strong>Manual Attendance:</strong> Your attendance may also be marked by officers or admins</li>
                  <li>Your attendance status will update immediately</li>
                </ol>
              </details>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- EXCUSES -->
          <div class="help-card">
            <div class="card-header">
              <h3>📝 Submit & Track Excuses</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-content">
              <details>
                <summary class="card-summary"><strong>How to Submit an Excuse</strong></summary>
                <p>Go to <%= link_to "Excuses", internal_excuses_path %> or submit directly from an event page.</p>
                <ol>
                  <li>Select the <strong>event</strong> you're excusing from</li>
                  <li>Type a <strong>brief reason</strong> (why you cannot/could not attend)</li>
                  <li>Attach a <strong>proof link</strong> (Google Drive, photo link, etc.)</li>
                  <li>Click <strong>Submit</strong> — status starts as <em>Pending</em></li>
                </ol>
              </details>

              <details>
                <summary class="card-summary"><strong>Submit Bulk Excuses</strong></summary>
                <p>Need to excuse multiple events at once? Use the bulk excuse workflow:</p>
                <ol>
                  <li>Go to <%= link_to "Excuses", internal_excuses_path %> and look for the <strong>Bulk Excuse</strong> option</li>
                  <li>Select <strong>multiple events</strong> you need to excuse from</li>
                  <li>Enter a <strong>single reason</strong> that applies to all selected events</li>
                  <li>Attach <strong>proof</strong> for the bulk excuse</li>
                  <li>Click <strong>Submit</strong> — all excuses will be created with <em>Pending</em> status</li>
                </ol>
              </details>

              <details>
                <summary class="card-summary"><strong>Track Your Excuse Status</strong></summary>
                <p>On the <%= link_to "Excuses", internal_excuses_path %> page, filter and view all your excuses:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><span class="badge pending">Pending</span> — Waiting for officer/admin review</li>
                  <li><span class="badge approved">Approved</span> — Your absence is excused</li>
                  <li><span class="badge denied">Denied</span> — Excuse was not accepted</li>
                  <li><span class="badge awaiting">Awaiting Admin Approval</span> — Officer provisionally approved; director must finalize</li>
                </ul>
              </details>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- MUSIC DRIVE (members) -->
          <div class="help-card">
            <div class="card-header">
              <h3>🎼 Music Drive</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-content">
              <details>
              <summary class="card-summary"><strong>What is the Music Drive?</strong></summary>
              <p>The Music Drive is a shared Google Drive where the Singing Cadets keep scores, rehearsal tracks, and sheet music.</p>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Access:</strong> Click the Music Drive link in the navigation or open it directly: <%= link_to "Open Music Drive", "https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/17ccw2GrZ6-p6WRj1jZO8-kcFxNzuFY79", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener" %></li>
                <li><strong>Use:</strong> Download rehearsal files, review scores before practice, and upload any director/arranger-approved materials if you have upload permissions.</li>
                <li><strong>Permissions:</strong> If you need upload access or see a missing file, contact a director (see Contact section).</li>
              </ul>
              </details>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- DISCIPLINE POINTS -->
          <div class="help-card">
            <div class="card-header">
              <h3>⚠️ Discipline Points</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-content">
              <details>
                <summary class="card-summary"><strong>View Your Discipline Points</strong></summary>
                <p>Check <%= link_to "My Discipline Points", internal_my_demerits_path %> to see all points assigned to you.</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Reason:</strong> Why the point was assigned</li>
                  <li><strong>Date Assigned:</strong> When you received it</li>
                  <li><strong>Assigned By:</strong> Who issued the discipline point</li>
                </ul>
                <p><em>If you believe a record is incorrect, contact an officer or director to discuss.</em></p>
              </details>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- NAVIGATION -->
          <div class="help-card">
            <div class="card-header">
              <h3>🧭 Quick Navigation</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-content">
              <ul class="nav-list">
                <li>🗓️ <%= link_to "Events", internal_events_path %></li>
                <li>📋 <%= link_to "Excuses", internal_excuses_path %></li>
                <li>🎵 <%= link_to "Music Drive", "https://drive.google.com/drive/u/3/folders/0ACAwK4ezZTfMUk9PVA", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener" %></li>
                <li>📌 <%= link_to "My Discipline Points", internal_my_demerits_path %></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>       
        </div>
      </section>
    <% end %>

    <% if current_user.officer? || current_user.admin? %>
      <!-- OFFICERS & ADMINS SECTION -->
      <section class="help-role-section">
        <div class="role-header">
          <h2>👮 Officer & Admin Guide</h2>
          <p>Tools and features for managing the organization</p>
        </div>

        <div class="help-grid">
          <!-- EVENTS MANAGEMENT -->
          <div class="help-card">
            <div class="card-header">
              <h3>📅 Event Management</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-content">
              <details>
                <summary class="card-summary"><strong>Create New Event</strong></summary>
                <p>Click <strong>New Event</strong> on the <%= link_to "Events", internal_events_path %> page.</p>
                <ol>
                  <li>Enter the <strong>event name</strong> (e.g., "Concert Performance")</li>
                  <li>Set the <strong>date and time</strong></li>
                  <li>Add a <strong>location</strong></li>
                  <li>Set any event-specific details (required attendance, notes, etc.)</li>
                  <li><strong>Self Check-in Code:</strong> Generate a unique code that members can use to automatically check themselves in — great for self-managed attendance!</li>
                  <li><strong>Recurring Events:</strong> Create repeating events by specifying the recurrence pattern (daily, weekly, monthly, etc.)</li>
                  <li>Click <strong>Create</strong> — members will see it immediately</li>
                </ol>
              </details>

              <details>
                <summary class="card-summary"><strong>View & Edit Events</strong></summary>
                <p>Go to <%= link_to "Events", internal_events_path %> to see all events. Click an event to view details and manage it.</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Edit Event:</strong> Change name, date, time, or location</li>
                  <li><strong>View Attendance:</strong> See who attended, was excused, or was absent</li>
                  <li><strong>Mark Attendance:</strong> Manually update attendance records if needed</li>
                </ul>
              </details>

              <details>
                <summary class="card-summary"><strong>Manage Event Attendance</strong></summary>
                <p>From an event's detail page:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>View Attendance List:</strong> See all members and their status</li>
                  <li><strong>Update Attendance:</strong> Manually mark members as attended, excused, or absent</li>
                  <li><strong>Approved Excuses:</strong> Approved excuses automatically update attendance as "excused"</li>
                  <li><strong>No-Show Follow-up:</strong> Track who didn't attend without an excuse</li>
                </ul>
              </details>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- EXCUSE MANAGEMENT -->
          <div class="help-card">
            <div class="card-header">
              <h3>📝 Excuse Review & Approval</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-content">
              <details>
                <summary class="card-summary"><strong>Review Submitted Excuses</strong></summary>
                <p>Go to <%= link_to "Excuses", internal_excuses_path %> to see all submitted excuses.</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Pending:</strong> Excuses waiting for your review</li>
                  <li><strong>Approved:</strong> Excuses you've accepted</li>
                  <li><strong>Denied:</strong> Excuses you've rejected</li>
                  <li><strong>Awaiting Admin Approval:</strong> Excuses that officers provisionally approved but need director finalization</li>
                </ul>
              </details>

              <details>
                <summary class="card-summary"><strong>Officer: Provisional Approve or Deny</strong></summary>
                <p>As an officer, you can provisionally approve or deny excuses:</p>
                <ol>
                  <li>Click an excuse from the <strong>Pending</strong> section to view full details (member name, event, reason, proof link)</li>
                  <li>Review the <strong>reason and proof</strong></li>
                  <li>Click <strong>Provisional Approve</strong> to recommend the excuse (status becomes <em>Awaiting Admin Approval</em>)</li>
                  <li>Or click <strong>Deny</strong> to reject it immediately</li>
                  <li><strong>Note:</strong> Provisionally approved excuses need director finalization before the member's attendance is updated</li>
                </ol>
              </details>

              <details>
                <summary class="card-summary"><strong>Director: Finalize Admin Approvals</strong></summary>
                <p>As a director, you review provisionally approved excuses:</p>
                <ol>
                  <li>Go to <%= link_to "Excuses", internal_excuses_path %> and view the <strong>Awaiting Admin Approval</strong> section</li>
                  <li>Click an excuse to review the officer's recommendation and member details</li>
                  <li>Click <strong>Approve</strong> to finalize the excuse (member attendance is automatically updated as "excused")</li>
                  <li>Or click <strong>Deny</strong> to reject it</li>
                  <li>Once finalized, the excuse is locked and member attendance reflects the decision</li>
                </ol>
              </details>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- DISCIPLINE MANAGEMENT -->
          <div class="help-card">
            <div class="card-header">
              <h3>⚠️ Discipline Points</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-content">
              <details>
                <summary class="card-summary"><strong>Create Discipline Points</strong></summary>
                <p>Go to <%= link_to "Discipline Points", internal_demerits_path %> and click <strong>New Discipline Point</strong>.</p>
                <ol>
                  <li>Select the <strong>member</strong> receiving the point</li>
                  <li>Enter the <strong>reason</strong> (what they did)</li>
                  <li>Add any <strong>notes</strong> for context</li>
                  <li>Click <strong>Create</strong></li>
                </ol>
              </details>

              <details>
                <summary class="card-summary"><strong>View & Edit Discipline Points</strong></summary>
                <p>On the <%= link_to "Discipline Points", internal_demerits_path %> page:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Search Members:</strong> Filter by member name to see their history</li>
                  <li><strong>View Details:</strong> Click a record to see who assigned it and when</li>
                  <li><strong>Edit/Delete:</strong> Modify or remove points if needed</li>
                </ul>
              </details>

              <details>
                <summary class="card-summary"><strong>Quick Add from Member Profile</strong></summary>
                <p>You can also assign discipline points directly from a member's profile page.</p>
              </details>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- MEMBER MANAGEMENT -->
          <div class="help-card">
            <div class="card-header">
              <h3>👥 Member Management</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-content">
              <details>
                <summary class="card-summary"><strong>View All Members</strong></summary>
                <p>Go to <%= link_to "Member Management", internal_users_path %> to see all members and their roles.</p>
              </details>

              <details>
                <summary class="card-summary"><strong>Edit Member Information</strong></summary>
                <p>Click a member to edit their:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Displayed Name</li>
                  <li>Role (Member, Officer, Admin)</li>
                  <li>Delete Member (remove their account from the system)</li>
                </ul>
              </details>

              <details>
                <summary class="card-summary"><strong>Change Member Roles</strong></summary>
                <p>From a member's profile, update their role to promote them to Officer or Admin status in order to grant them additional permissions and access within the system.</p>
              </details>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="help-card">
            <div class="card-header">
              <h3>⚙️ Registration Management</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-content">
              <details>
                <summary class="card-summary"><strong>Manage Sign-ups</strong></summary>
                <p>Go to <%= link_to "Registrations", admin_registrations_path %> to handle new member registrations.</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Pending Members:</strong> View member information awaiting approval</li>
                  <li><strong>Pending Registrations:</strong> Accept or reject new signups</li>
                </ul>
              </details>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- NAVIGATION -->
          <div class="help-card">
            <div class="card-header">
              <h3>🧭 Quick Navigation</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-content">
              <ul class="nav-list">
                <li>🗓️ <%= link_to "Events", internal_events_path %></li>
                <li>📋 <%= link_to "Excuses", internal_excuses_path %></li>
                <li>🎵 <%= link_to "Music Drive", "https://drive.google.com/drive/u/3/folders/0ACAwK4ezZTfMUk9PVA", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener" %></li>
                <li>👥 <%= link_to "Member Management", internal_users_path %></li>
                <li>⚠️ <%= link_to "Discipline Points", internal_demerits_path %></li>
                <li>⚙️ <%= link_to "Registration Approval", admin_registrations_path %></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    <% end %>
  <% end %>

  <!-- TRAINING VIDEOS -->
  <section class="help-role-section">
    <div class="role-header">
      <h2>🎥 Training Videos</h2>
      <p>Learn by watching — click "Watch" to open the video in a new tab</p>
    </div>

    <div class="help-grid">
      <% if user_signed_in? && current_user.user? %>
        <!-- Member Videos (list with Watch button) -->
        <div class="help-card">
          <div class="card-header">
            <h3>Member Videos</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="card-content">
            <ul class="training-list">
              <li class="training-item">
                <div class="training-meta">
                  <strong>Getting Started Basics</strong><br>
                  <small>Quick tour of the app and where to find things.</small>
                </div>
                <%= link_to "Watch", "https://drive.google.com/file/d/19T8RGxsmZlMS7REbrsQ744Cm0rTzZPB2/view?usp=sharing", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener", class: "video-btn" %>
              </li>

              <li class="training-item">
                <div class="training-meta">
                  <strong>Submitting & Tracking Excuses</strong><br>
                  <small>How to submit single or bulk excuses and check their status.</small>
                </div>
                <%= link_to "Watch", "https://drive.google.com/file/d/19T8RGxsmZlMS7REbrsQ744Cm0rTzZPB2/view?usp=sharing&t=200", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener", class: "video-btn" %>
              </li>

              <li class="training-item">
                <div class="training-meta">
                  <strong>Checking In to Events</strong><br>
                  <small>Using self check-in codes and confirming attendance.</small>
                </div>
                <%= link_to "Watch", "https://drive.google.com/file/d/19T8RGxsmZlMS7REbrsQ744Cm0rTzZPB2/view?usp=sharing&t=331", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener", class: "video-btn" %>
              </li>

              <li class="training-item">
                <div class="training-meta">
                  <strong>Understanding Discipline Points</strong><br>
                  <small>View and interpret your discipline records.</small>
                </div>
                <%= link_to "Watch", "https://drive.google.com/file/d/19T8RGxsmZlMS7REbrsQ744Cm0rTzZPB2/view?usp=sharing&t=404", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener", class: "video-btn" %>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

      <% elsif user_signed_in? && (current_user.officer? || current_user.admin?) %>
        <!-- Member Videos (for officers/admins) -->
        <div class="help-card">
          <div class="card-header">
            <h3>Member Videos</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="card-content">
            <ul class="training-list">
              <li class="training-item">
                <div class="training-meta"><strong>Getting Started Basics</strong></div>
                <%= link_to "Watch", "https://drive.google.com/file/d/19T8RGxsmZlMS7REbrsQ744Cm0rTzZPB2/view?usp=sharing", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener", class: "video-btn" %>
              </li>
              <li class="training-item">
                <div class="training-meta"><strong>Submitting & Tracking Excuses</strong></div>
                <%= link_to "Watch", "https://drive.google.com/file/d/19T8RGxsmZlMS7REbrsQ744Cm0rTzZPB2/view?usp=sharing&t=200", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener", class: "video-btn" %>
              </li>
              <li class="training-item">
                <div class="training-meta"><strong>Checking In to Events</strong></div>
                <%= link_to "Watch", "https://drive.google.com/file/d/19T8RGxsmZlMS7REbrsQ744Cm0rTzZPB2/view?usp=sharing&t=331", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener", class: "video-btn" %>
              </li>
              <li class="training-item">
                <div class="training-meta"><strong>Understanding Discipline Points</strong></div>
                <%= link_to "Watch", "https://drive.google.com/file/d/19T8RGxsmZlMS7REbrsQ744Cm0rTzZPB2/view?usp=sharing&t=404", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener", class: "video-btn" %>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Officer/Admin Videos -->
        <div class="help-card">
          <div class="card-header">
            <h3>Officer/Admin Videos</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="card-content">
            <ul class="training-list">
              <li class="training-item">
                <div class="training-meta"><strong>Registrations & Member Management</strong></div>
                <%= link_to "Watch", "https://drive.google.com/file/d/1jfaWoEmHxI6s2Eva8_djz3jk8ajrYv3t/view?usp=sharing", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener", class: "video-btn" %>
              </li>
              <li class="training-item">
                <div class="training-meta"><strong>Creating/Editing Events & Self Check-in Codes</strong></div>
                <%= link_to "Watch", "https://drive.google.com/file/d/1jfaWoEmHxI6s2Eva8_djz3jk8ajrYv3t/view?usp=sharing&t=56", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener", class: "video-btn" %>
              </li>
              <li class="training-item">
                <div class="training-meta"><strong>Attendance Management & Absence Report</strong></div>
                <%= link_to "Watch", "https://drive.google.com/file/d/1jfaWoEmHxI6s2Eva8_djz3jk8ajrYv3t/view?usp=sharing&t=210", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener", class: "video-btn" %>
              </li>
              <li class="training-item">
                <div class="training-meta"><strong>Reviewing & Provisionally Approving Excuses</strong></div>
                <%= link_to "Watch", "https://drive.google.com/file/d/1jfaWoEmHxI6s2Eva8_djz3jk8ajrYv3t/view?usp=sharing&t=277", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener", class: "video-btn" %>
              </li>
              <li class="training-item">
                <div class="training-meta"><strong>Admin Finalization of Excuses</strong></div>
                <%= link_to "Watch", "https://drive.google.com/file/d/1jfaWoEmHxI6s2Eva8_djz3jk8ajrYv3t/view?usp=sharing&t=366", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener", class: "video-btn" %>
              </li>
              <li class="training-item">
                <div class="training-meta"><strong>Discipline Points Management</strong></div>
                <%= link_to "Watch", "https://drive.google.com/file/d/1jfaWoEmHxI6s2Eva8_djz3jk8ajrYv3t/view?usp=sharing&t=448", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener", class: "video-btn" %>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CONTACT SECTION -->
  <section class="help-role-section">
    <div class="role-header">
      <h2>💬 Need Help?</h2>
      <p>Contact the right person for your question</p>
    </div>
    
    <% if user_signed_in? && current_user.user? %>
      <div class="contact-card member-contact">
        <h3>👋 Get in Touch with Leadership</h3>
        <p>For questions, issues, or concerns, please reach out to the director:</p>
        <div class="contact-info">
          <p><strong>Director</strong><br>David Kipp — <code>dkipp@tamu.edu</code></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    <% else %>
      <div class="contact-card dev-contact">
        <h3>👨‍💻 Developer Team</h3>
        <p>If you're an officer or admin and found a bug or have a technical issue, please contact one of the developers:</p>
        <div class="contact-info">
          <ul class="dev-list">
            <li>Jessica Jakubik — <code>jessjakubik@tamu.edu</code></li>
            <li>Owen Brown — <code>owenbrown@tamu.edu</code></li>
            <li>Anjali Varghese — <code>anjali@tamu.edu</code></li>
            <li>Taylor Smith — <code>smith.taylor@tamu.edu</code></li>
            <li>Lucas Bryant — <code>lucas_bryant1@tamu.edu</code></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    <% end %>
  </section>
</div>

<style>
  .help-container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 40px 20px;
    font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f5f7fa 0%, #c3cfe2 100%);
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  .help-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 50px;
  }

  .help-header h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    color: #2c3e50;
    margin: 0 0 10px 0;
  }

  .help-header p {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: #555;
  }

  .help-role-section {
    margin-bottom: 50px;
  }

  .role-header {
    margin-bottom: 30px;
    padding-bottom: 15px;
    border-bottom: 3px solid #500000;
  }

  .role-header h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: #2c3e50;
    margin: 0 0 5px 0;
  }

  .role-header p {
    color: #666;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .help-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(350px, 1fr));
    gap: 25px;
    margin-bottom: 30px;
  }

  .help-card {
    background: white;
    border-radius: 12px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
  }

